    {
      "id": "4cSPsRIftTyYX8Kf6ssCz",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 447,
      "y": 253.5,
      "width": 647.8595581054688,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0O",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1063318690,
      "version": 71,
      "versionNonce": 1724305122,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1783943891563,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Requirements -> Entities -> API -> High Level Design -> Deep Dive",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Requirements -> Entities -> API -> High Level Design -> Deep Dive",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "u_XSjyXIyxqbmdki4z9PI",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 537,
      "y": 300.5,
      "width": 899.199462890625,
      "height": 650,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0P",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 723471842,
      "version": 1099,
      "versionNonce": 863119970,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1783945304764,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Functional Requirements\n\n1. User should be able to input a start location and destination and get an estimated fare.\n2. User should be able to request a ride based on an estimate\n3. Drivers should be able to accept/deny the ride request\n4. Drivers should be able to navigte to pickup and drop off\n\n\n-- Out of Scope\n1. Multiple car types\n2. Rating for drivers and riders\n3. Schedule a ride in advance\n\nNon Functional requirements\n\n1. low latency matching - less than 1 minute to match rider to driver\n2. consistency for 1:1 rider to driver matching. Any given ride is matched to one rider\n3. Highly available outside matching (reduce downtime)\\\n4. Handle high throughput (surges for peak hours), thousands of requests in a given region\\\n\n-- Out of Scope\n1. GDPR\n2. User Privany\n3. Resilience\n4. Monitoring, logging, alerting\n5. Deployment",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Functional Requirements\n\n1. User should be able to input a start location and destination and get an estimated fare.\n2. User should be able to request a ride based on an estimate\n3. Drivers should be able to accept/deny the ride request\n4. Drivers should be able to navigte to pickup and drop off\n\n\n-- Out of Scope\n1. Multiple car types\n2. Rating for drivers and riders\n3. Schedule a ride in advance\n\nNon Functional requirements\n\n1. low latency matching - less than 1 minute to match rider to driver\n2. consistency for 1:1 rider to driver matching. Any given ride is matched to one rider\n3. Highly available outside matching (reduce downtime)\\\n4. Handle high throughput (surges for peak hours), thousands of requests in a given region\\\n\n-- Out of Scope\n1. GDPR\n2. User Privany\n3. Resilience\n4. Monitoring, logging, alerting\n5. Deployment",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "BPsraGR09JJjnZUA8ei2I",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1906,
      "y": 234.5,
      "width": 611.299560546875,
      "height": 1350,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0Q",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 319272702,
      "version": 1006,
      "versionNonce": 1246235582,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1783945370829,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "\n\n\nAPIs\n\n1. POST /ride/fare-estimate -> Partial<Ride>\n{\n    source coordinates\n    destination coordinates\n}\n\nResponse:\n{\n    rideId\n    approximateFare\n}\n\n\n\n2. PATCH /ride/request\n{\n    rideId\n}\n\nstatus 200/400 (Async)\n\n\nPOST /location/update -> Driver should send every n seconds\n{\n    driverLat,\n    driverLong\n}\n\n\n\n3. PATCH /ride/driver/accept\n{\n    rideId\n    true/false\n}\n\n\n\n4. PATCH ride/driver/update\n{\n    rideId\n    stauts: pickedup: droppedoff\n}\n\nResponse:\n{\n    destinationlat\n    destinationlong\n}",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "\n\n\nAPIs\n\n1. POST /ride/fare-estimate -> Partial<Ride>\n{\n    source coordinates\n    destination coordinates\n}\n\nResponse:\n{\n    rideId\n    approximateFare\n}\n\n\n\n2. PATCH /ride/request\n{\n    rideId\n}\n\nstatus 200/400 (Async)\n\n\nPOST /location/update -> Driver should send every n seconds\n{\n    driverLat,\n    driverLong\n}\n\n\n\n3. PATCH /ride/driver/accept\n{\n    rideId\n    true/false\n}\n\n\n\n4. PATCH ride/driver/update\n{\n    rideId\n    stauts: pickedup: droppedoff\n}\n\nResponse:\n{\n    destinationlat\n    destinationlong\n}",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
